section
  h2 XHTML is a bad idea

  ul
    li <b>Internet Explorer</b> doesn't support XHTML
    li There is no <b>error handling</b>
    li The <b>JavaScript code</b> must be inside a CDATA block
    li The <b>entities</b> (&amp;amp;) must be escaped
    li In general, there is <b>no advantage in XHTML</b>

section
  h2 XHTML vs HTML

  ul.read-block
    li <b>Case sensitive</b>
    li <b>Void entities:</b> img, br, hr
    li <b>Unexpected end tags:</b> #{'</br> </p>'}
    li <b>Unescaped & and &lt;</b>
    li <b>CDATA elements</b>: script and style

section
  h2 XHTML vs HTML (II)
  .row-fluid
    .span6
      p <b>XHTML</b>
      pre
        code.
          #{'<p>Hello</p>'}
          #{'<p>world</p>'}
          #{'<img src="hello?foo=1&amp;amp;bar=2"/>'}
          #{'<script type="text/javascript">'}
          #{'<![CDATA['}
          ... unescaped script content ...
          ]]>
          #{'</script>'}
    .span6
      p <b>HTML</b>
      pre
        code.
          #{'<p>'}Hello
          #{'<p>'}world
          #{'<IMG src="hello?foo=1&bar=2">'}
          #{'<script>'}
          ... unescaped script content ...
          #{'</script>'}

